'''= Local Production, Local Consumption'''


Originally a concept in agriculture to create a sustainable economy, but it can be applied to the economy as a whole.


=Discussion=

A group of Japanese researchers has propoped a five-layer P2P architecture to realize LPLC.

URL = http://www.media-art-online.org/pdf/das-p2p2007-lplc.pdf

Reference: Local Production, Local Consumption Peer-to-Peer Architecture for a Dependable and Sustainable Social Infrastructure. By Saito, K.; Morino, E.; Suko, Y.; Suzuki, T.; Murai, J.;Applications and the Internet Workshops, 2007. SAINT Workshops 2007.
International Symposium on Jan. 2007 Page(s):58 - 58

Abstract: "Peer-to-peer (P2P) is a system of overlay networks such that
participants can potentially take symmetrical roles. This translates
itself into a design based on the philosophy of local production, local
consumption (LPLC), originally an agricultural concept to promote
sustainable local economy. This philosophy helps enhancing survivability
of a society by providing a dependable economic infrastructure and
promoting the power of individuals. This paper attempts to put existing
works of P2P designs into the perspective of the five-layer architecture
model to realize LPLC, and proposes future research directions toward
integration of P2P studies for actualization of a dependable and
sustainable social infrastructure."


